11253 qPrint(ext),qPrint(language));
11254 }
11255 else
11256 {

11258 qPrint(ext),qPrint(language));
11259 }
11260 }
11261 }

11271 }

11275 }

11286 }

11292 {
11293 continue;
11294 }

◆ findEndOfTemplate()

static int findEndOfTemplate ( const QCString &  s,
int  startPos 
)
static

Searches for the end of a template in prototype s starting from character position startPos. If the end was found the position of the closing > is returned, otherwise -1 is returned.

Handles exotic cases such as

Class<(id<0)>
Class<bits<<2>
Class<"<">
Class<'<'>
Class<(")<")>
MemberListContainer::Class
@ Class

Definition at line 4262 of file doxygen.cpp.

4263{
4264 // locate end of template
4265 int e=startPos;
4266 int brCount=1;
4267 int roundCount=0;
4268 int len = s.length();
4269 bool insideString=FALSE;
4270 bool insideChar=FALSE;
4271 char pc = 0;
4272 while (e<len && brCount!=0)
4273 {
4274 char c=s.at(e);
4275 switch(c)
4276 {
4277 case '<':
4278 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4279 {
4280 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='<')
4281 e++;
4282 else if (roundCount==0)
4283 brCount++;
4284 }
4285 break;
4286 case '>':
4287 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4288 {
4289 if (e<len-1 && s.at(e+1)=='>')
4290 e++;
4291 else if (roundCount==0)
4292 brCount--;
4293 }
4294 break;
4295 case '(':
4296 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4297 roundCount++;
4298 break;
4299 case ')':
4300 if (!insideString && !insideChar)
4301 roundCount--;
4302 break;
4303 case '"':
4304 if (!insideChar)
4305 {
4306 if (insideString && pc!='\\')
4307 insideString=FALSE;
4308 else
4309 insideString=TRUE;
4310 }
4311 break;
4312 case '\'':
4313 if (!insideString)
4314 {
4315 if (insideChar && pc!='\\')
4316 insideChar=FALSE;
4317 else
4318 insideChar=TRUE;
4319 }
4320 break;
4321 }
4322 pc = c;
4323 e++;
4324 }
4325 return brCount==0 ? e : -1;
4326}

This function tries to find a member (in a documented class/file/namespace) that corresponds to the function/variable declaration given in funcDecl.

The boolean overloaded is used to specify whether or not a standard overload documentation line should be generated.

The boolean isFunc is a hint that indicates that this is a function instead of a variable or typedef.

2864
2865 //int indentDepth=0;
2866 int si=scope.find('@');
2867 //int anonyScopes = 0;
2868 //bool added=FALSE;
2869
2870 bool inlineSimpleStructs = Config_getBool(INLINE_SIMPLE_STRUCTS);
2871 Relationship relationship = isMemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
2872 isRelated ? Relationship::Related :
2873 Relationship::Member ;
2874 if (si!=-1 && !inlineSimpleStructs) // anonymous scope or type
2875 {
2876 QCString pScope;
2877 ClassDefMutable *pcd=0;
2878 pScope = scope.left(std::max(si-2,0)); // scope without tag less parts
2879 if (!pScope.isEmpty())
2880 pScope.prepend(annScopePrefix);
2881 else if (annScopePrefix.length()>2)
2882 pScope=annScopePrefix.left(annScopePrefix.length()-2);
2883 if (name.at(0)!='@')
2884 {
2885 if (!pScope.isEmpty() && (pcd=getClassMutable(pScope)))
2886 {
2887 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Adding anonymous member to scope '{}'",pScope);
2888 md=addVariableToClass(root, // entry
2889 pcd, // class to add member to
2890 mtype, // member type
2891 type, // type value as string
2892 name, // member name
2893 args, // arguments as string
2894 TRUE, // from anonymous scope
2895 0, // from anonymous member
2896 root->protection,
2897 relationship
2898 );
2899 //added=TRUE;
2900 }
2901 else // anonymous scope inside namespace or file => put variable in the global scope
2902 {
2903 if (mtype==MemberType_Variable)
2904 {
2905 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("Adding anonymous member to global scope '{}'");
2906 md=addVariableToFile(root,mtype,pScope,type,name,args,TRUE,0);
2907 }
2908 //added=TRUE;
2909 }
2910 }
2911 }
2912
2913 addVariableToClass(root, // entry
2914 cd, // class to add member to
2915 mtype, // member type
2916 type, // type value as string
2917 name, // name of the member
2918 args, // arguments as string
2919 FALSE, // from anonymous scope
2920 md, // from anonymous member
2921 root->protection,
2922 relationship
2923 );
2924 }
2925 else if (!name.isEmpty()) // global variable
2926 {
2927 addVariableToFile(root,mtype,scope,type,name,args,FALSE,/*0,*/0);
2928 }
2929
2930}

2932//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2933// Searches the Entry tree for typedef documentation sections.
2934// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
2935static void buildTypedefList(const Entry *root)
2936{
2937 //printf("buildVarList(%s)\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()));
2938 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
2939 root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
2940 root->type.find("typedef ")!=-1 // its a typedef
2941 )
2942 {
2943 AUTO_TRACE();
2944 addVariable(root);
2945 }
2946 for (const auto &e : root->children())
2947 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
2948 buildTypedefList(e.get());
2949}

2957 root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC &&
2958 root->type.find("sequence<")!=-1 // it's a sequence
2959 )
2960 {
2961 AUTO_TRACE();
2962 addVariable(root);
2963 }

2965 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)

2987//----------------------------------------------------------------------
2988// Searches the Entry tree for Variable documentation sections.
2989// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
2990
2991static void buildVarList(const Entry *root)
2992{
2993 //printf("buildVarList(%s) section=%08x\n",qPrint(rootNav->name()),rootNav->section());
2994 int isFuncPtr=-1;
2995 if (!root->name.isEmpty() &&
2996 (root->type.isEmpty() || g_compoundKeywords.find(root->type.str())==g_compoundKeywords.end()) &&
2997 (
2998 (root->section==Entry::VARIABLE_SEC // it's a variable
2999 ) ||
3000 (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // or maybe a function pointer variable
3001 (isFuncPtr=findFunctionPtr(root->type.str(),root->lang))!=-1
3002 ) ||
3003 (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC && // class variable initialized by constructor
3004 isVarWithConstructor(root)
3005 )
3006 )
3007 ) // documented variable
3008 {
3009 AUTO_TRACE();
3010 addVariable(root,isFuncPtr);
3011 }
3012 for (const auto &e : root->children())
3013 if (e->section!=Entry::ENUM_SEC)
3014 buildVarList(e.get());
3015}

3017//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3018// Searches the Entry tree for Interface sections (UNO IDL only).
3019// If found they are stored in their service or in the global list.
3020//
3021
3022static void addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(
3023 const Entry *root,
3024 ClassDefMutable *cd,
3025 QCString const& rname)
3026{
3027 FileDef *fd = root->fileDef();
3028 enum MemberType type = (root->section==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC)
3029 ? MemberType_Interface
3030 : MemberType_Service;
3031 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3032 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3033 {
3034 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3035 }
3036 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3037 fileName, root->startLine, root->startColumn, root->type, rname,
3038 "", "", root->protection, root->virt, root->isStatic, Relationship::Member,
3039 type, ArgumentList(), root->argList, root->metaData) };
3040 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3041 md->setMemberClass(cd);
3042 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3043 md->setDocsForDefinition(false);
3044 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3045 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3046 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3047 md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3048 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3049 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3050 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3051 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3052 md->setFileDef(fd);
3053 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3054 QCString const def = root->type + " " + rname;
3055 md->setDefinition(def);
3056 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3057 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3058 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3059 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3060 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3061
3062 AUTO_TRACE("Interface member: fileName='{}' type='{}' name='{}' mtype='{}' prot={} virt={} state={} proto={} def='{}'",
3063 fileName,root->type,rname,type,root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,root->proto,def);
3064
3065 // add member to the class cd
3066 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3067 // also add the member as a "base" (to get nicer diagrams)
3068 // "optional" interface/service get Protected which turns into dashed line
3069 BaseInfo base(rname,
3070 (root->spec & (Entry::Optional)) ? Protection::Protected : Protection::Public, Specifier::Normal);
3071 TemplateNameMap templateNames;
3072 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,DocumentedOnly,true) ||
3073 findClassRelation(root,cd,cd,&base,templateNames,Undocumented,true);
3074 // add file to list of used files
3075 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3076
3077 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3078 root->markAsProcessed();
3079 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3080
3081 // add member to the global list of all members
3082 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(rname);
3083 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3084}
3085
3086static void buildInterfaceAndServiceList(const Entry *root)
3087{
3088 if (root->section==Entry::EXPORTED_INTERFACE_SEC ||
3089 root->section==Entry::INCLUDED_SERVICE_SEC)
3090 {
3091 AUTO_TRACE("Exported interface/included service: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}'"
3092 " relates='{}' relatesType='{}' file='{}' line={} bodyLine={} #tArgLists={}"
3093 " mGrpId={} spec={:#x} proto={} docFile='{}'",
3094 root->type, root->parent()->name, root->name, root->args,
3095 root->relates, root->relatesType, root->fileName, root->startLine, root->bodyLine, root->tArgLists.size(),
3096 root->mGrpId, root->spec, root->proto, root->docFile);
3097
3098 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3099
3100 if (!rname.isEmpty())
3101 {
3102 QCString scope = root->parent()->name;
3103 ClassDefMutable *cd = getClassMutable(scope);
3104 assert(cd);
3105 if (cd && ((ClassDef::Interface == cd->compoundType()) ||
3106 (ClassDef::Service == cd->compoundType()) ||
3107 (ClassDef::Singleton == cd->compoundType())))
3108 {
3109 addInterfaceOrServiceToServiceOrSingleton(root,cd,rname);
3110 }
3111 else
3112 {
3113 assert(false); // was checked by scanner.l
3114 }
3115 }
3116 else if (rname.isEmpty())
3117 {
3118 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3119 "Illegal member name found.");
3120 }
3121 }
3122 // can only have these in IDL anyway
3123 switch (root->lang)
3124 {
3125 case SrcLangExt_Unknown: // fall through (root node always is Unknown)
3126 case SrcLangExt_IDL:
3127 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildInterfaceAndServiceList(e.get());
3128 break;
3129 default:
3130 return; // nothing to do here
3131 }
3132}

3135//----------------------------------------------------------------------
3136// Searches the Entry tree for Function sections.
3137// If found they are stored in their class or in the global list.
3138
3139static void addMethodToClass(const Entry *root,ClassDefMutable *cd,
3140 const QCString &rtype,const QCString &rname,const QCString &rargs,
3141 bool isFriend,
3142 Protection protection,bool stat,Specifier virt,uint64_t spec,
3143 const QCString &relates
3144 )
3145{
3146 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3147
3148 QCString type = rtype;
3149 QCString args = rargs;
3150
3151 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3152 name.stripPrefix("::");
3153
3154 MemberType mtype;
3155 if (isFriend) mtype=MemberType_Friend;
3156 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Signal) mtype=MemberType_Signal;
3157 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::Slot) mtype=MemberType_Slot;
3158 else if (root->mtype==MethodTypes::DCOP) mtype=MemberType_DCOP;
3159 else mtype=MemberType_Function;
3160
3161 // strip redundant template specifier for constructors
3162 int i = -1;
3163 int j = -1;
3164 if ((fd==0 || fd->getLanguage()==SrcLangExt_Cpp) &&
3165 !name.startsWith("operator ") && // not operator
3166 (i=name.find('<'))!=-1 && // containing <
3167 (j=name.find('>'))!=-1 && // or >
3168 (j!=i+2 || name.at(i+1)!='=') // but not the C++20 spaceship operator <=>
3169 )
3170 {
3171 name=name.left(i);
3172 }
3173
3174 QCString fileName = root->fileName;
3175 if (fileName.isEmpty() && root->tagInfo())
3176 {
3177 fileName = root->tagInfo()->tagName;
3178 }
3179
3180 //printf("root->name='%s; args='%s' root->argList='%s'\n",
3181 // qPrint(root->name),qPrint(args),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList))
3182 // );
3183
3184 // adding class member
3185 Relationship relationship = relates.isEmpty() ? Relationship::Member :
3186 root->relatesType==RelatesType::MemberOf ? Relationship::Foreign :
3187 Relationship::Related ;
3188 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3189 fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3190 type,name,args,root->exception,
3191 protection,virt,
3192 stat && root->relatesType!=RelatesType::MemberOf,
3193 relationship,
3194 mtype,!root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3195 root->argList, root->metaData) };
3196 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3197 md->setMemberClass(cd);
3198 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3199 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3200 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3201 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3202 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3203 md->setMemberSpecifiers(spec);
3204 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3205 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3206 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3207 md->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3208 md->setId(root->id);
3209 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3210 md->setFileDef(fd);
3211 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3212 QCString def;
3213 QCString qualScope = cd->qualifiedNameWithTemplateParameters();
3214 SrcLangExt lang = cd->getLanguage();
3215 QCString scopeSeparator=getLanguageSpecificSeparator(lang);
3216 if (scopeSeparator!="::")
3217 {
3218 qualScope = substitute(qualScope,"::",scopeSeparator);
3219 }
3220 if (lang==SrcLangExt_PHP)
3221 {
3222 // for PHP we use Class::method and Namespace\method
3223 scopeSeparator="::";
3224 }
3225// QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? args : QCString();
3226 if (!relates.isEmpty() || isFriend || Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES))
3227 {
3228 if (!type.isEmpty())
3229 {
3230 def=type+" "+name; //+optArgs;
3231 }
3232 else
3233 {
3234 def=name; //+optArgs;
3235 }
3236 }
3237 else
3238 {
3239 if (!type.isEmpty())
3240 {
3241 def=type+" "+qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3242 }
3243 else
3244 {
3245 def=qualScope+scopeSeparator+name; //+optArgs;
3246 }
3247 }
3248 def.stripPrefix("friend ");
3249 md->setDefinition(def);
3250 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3251 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3252 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3253 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3254 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3255
3256 AUTO_TRACE("function member: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' proto={} def='{}'",
3257 type, qualScope, rname, args, root->proto, def);
3258
3259 // add member to the class cd
3260 cd->insertMember(md.get());
3261 // add file to list of used files
3262 cd->insertUsedFile(fd);
3263
3264 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3265 root->markAsProcessed();
3266 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3267
3268 // add member to the global list of all members
3269 //printf("Adding member=%s class=%s\n",qPrint(md->name()),qPrint(cd->name()));
3270 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::memberNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3271 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3272}

3274//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3275
3276static void addGlobalFunction(const Entry *root,const QCString &rname,const QCString &sc)
3277{
3278 QCString scope = sc;
3279
3280 // new global function
3281 QCString name=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(rname);
3282 std::unique_ptr<MemberDefMutable> md { createMemberDef(
3283 root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn,
3284 root->type,name,root->args,root->exception,
3285 root->protection,root->virt,root->isStatic,Relationship::Member,
3286 MemberType_Function,
3287 !root->tArgLists.empty() ? root->tArgLists.back() : ArgumentList(),
3288 root->argList,root->metaData) };
3289
3290 md->setTagInfo(root->tagInfo());
3291 md->setLanguage(root->lang);
3292 md->setId(root->id);
3293 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3294 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3295 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3296 md->setPrototype(root->proto,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3297 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3298 md->setTypeConstraints(root->typeConstr);
3299 //md->setBody(root->body);
3300 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3301 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3302 md->setBodyDef(fd);
3303 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3304 md->setMemberSpecifiers(root->spec);
3305 md->setMemberGroupId(root->mGrpId);
3306 md->setRequiresClause(root->req);
3307
3308 NamespaceDefMutable *nd = 0;
3309 // see if the function is inside a namespace that was not part of
3310 // the name already (in that case nd should be non-zero already)
3311 if (root->parent()->section == Entry::NAMESPACE_SEC )
3312 {
3313 //QCString nscope=removeAnonymousScopes(root->parent()->name);
3314 QCString nscope=root->parent()->name;
3315 if (!nscope.isEmpty())
3316 {
3317 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(nscope);
3318 }
3319 }
3320 else if (root->parent()->section==Entry::GROUPDOC_SEC && !scope.isEmpty())
3321 {
3322 nd = getResolvedNamespaceMutable(sc);
3323 }
3324
3325 if (!scope.isEmpty())
3326 {
3327 QCString sep = getLanguageSpecificSeparator(root->lang);
3328 if (sep!="::")
3329 {
3330 scope = substitute(scope,"::",sep);
3331 }
3332 scope+=sep;
3333 }
3334
3335 if (Config_getBool(HIDE_SCOPE_NAMES)) scope = "";
3336 QCString def;
3337 //QCString optArgs = root->argList.empty() ? QCString() : root->args;
3338 if (!root->type.isEmpty())
3339 {
3340 def=root->type+" "+scope+name; //+optArgs;
3341 }
3342 else
3343 {
3344 def=scope+name; //+optArgs;
3345 }
3346 AUTO_TRACE("new non-member function type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' proto={} def='{}'",
3347 root->type,scope,rname,root->args,root->proto,def);
3348 md->setDefinition(def);
3349 md->enableCallGraph(root->callGraph);
3350 md->enableCallerGraph(root->callerGraph);
3351 md->enableReferencedByRelation(root->referencedByRelation);
3352 md->enableReferencesRelation(root->referencesRelation);
3353 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3354
3355 md->setRefItems(root->sli);
3356 if (nd && !nd->name().isEmpty() && nd->name().at(0)!='@')
3357 {
3358 // add member to namespace
3359 md->setNamespace(nd);
3360 nd->insertMember(md.get());
3361 }
3362 if (fd)
3363 {
3364 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3365 // inserted it into the namespace)
3366 md->setFileDef(fd);
3367 fd->insertMember(md.get());
3368 }
3369
3370 addMemberToGroups(root,md.get());
3371 if (root->relatesType == RelatesType::Simple) // if this is a relatesalso command,
3372 // allow find Member to pick it up
3373 {
3374 root->markAsProcessed(); // Otherwise we have finished with this entry.
3375 }
3376
3377 // add member to the list of file members
3378 MemberName *mn = Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->add(name);
3379 mn->push_back(std::move(md));
3380}
3381
3382//------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3383
3384static void buildFunctionList(const Entry *root)
3385{
3386 if (root->section==Entry::FUNCTION_SEC)
3387 {
3388 AUTO_TRACE("member function: type='{}' scope='{}' name='{}' args='{}' relates='{}' relatesType='{}'"
3389 " file='{}' line={} bodyLine={} #tArgLists={} mGrpId={}"
3390 " spec={:#x} proto={} docFile='{}'",
3391 root->type, root->parent()->name, root->name, root->args, root->relates, root->relatesType,
3392 root->fileName, root->startLine, root->bodyLine, root->tArgLists.size(), root->mGrpId,
3393 root->spec, root->proto, root->docFile);
3394
3395 bool isFriend=root->type.find("friend ")!=-1;
3396 QCString rname = removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->name);
3397 //printf("rname=%s\n",qPrint(rname));
3398
3399 QCString scope;
3400 int index = computeQualifiedIndex(rname);
3401 if (index!=-1 && root->parent()->section==Entry::GROUPDOC_SEC && root->parent()->tagInfo())
3402 // grouped members are stored with full scope
3403 {
3404 buildScopeFromQualifiedName(rname.left(index+2),root->lang,root->tagInfo());
3405 scope=rname.left(index);
3406 rname=rname.mid(index+2);
3407 }
3408 else
3409 {
3410 scope=root->parent()->name; //stripAnonymousNamespaceScope(root->parent->name);
3411 }
3412 if (!rname.isEmpty() && scope.find('@')==-1)
3413 {
3414 ClassDefMutable *cd=0;
3415 // check if this function's parent is a class
3416 scope=stripTemplateSpecifiersFromScope(scope,FALSE);
3417
3418 FileDef *rfd=root->fileDef();
3419
3420 int memIndex=rname.findRev("::");
3421
3422 cd=getClassMutable(scope);
3423 if (cd && scope+"::"==rname.left(scope.length()+2)) // found A::f inside A
3424 {
3425 // strip scope from name
3426 rname=rname.right(rname.length()-root->parent()->name.length()-2);
3427 }
3428
3429 bool isMember=FALSE;
3430 if (memIndex!=-1)
3431 {
3432 int ts=rname.find('<');
3433 int te=rname.find('>');
3434 if (memIndex>0 && (ts==-1 || te==-1))
3435 {
3436 // note: the following code was replaced by inMember=TRUE to deal with a
3437 // function rname='X::foo' of class X inside a namespace also called X...
3438 // bug id 548175
3439 //nd = Doxygen::namespaceLinkedMap->find(rname.left(memIndex));
3440 //isMember = nd==0;
3441 //if (nd)
3442 //{
3443 // // strip namespace scope from name
3444 // scope=rname.left(memIndex);
3445 // rname=rname.right(rname.length()-memIndex-2);
3446 //}
3447 isMember = TRUE;
3448 }
3449 else
3450 {
3451 isMember=memIndex<ts || memIndex>te;
3452 }
3453 }
3454
3455 if (!root->parent()->name.isEmpty() &&
3456 (root->parent()->section & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK) &&
3457 cd
3458 )
3459 {
3460 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("member '{}' of class '{}'", rname,cd->name());
3461 addMethodToClass(root,cd,root->type,rname,root->args,isFriend,
3462 root->protection,root->isStatic,root->virt,root->spec,root->relates);
3463 }
3464 else if (!((root->parent()->section & Entry::COMPOUND_MASK)
3465 || root->parent()->section==Entry::OBJCIMPL_SEC
3466 ) &&
3467 !isMember &&
3468 (root->relates.isEmpty() || root->relatesType==RelatesType::Duplicate) &&
3469 !root->type.startsWith("extern ") && !root->type.startsWith("typedef ")
3470 )
3471 // no member => unrelated function
3472 {
3473 /* check the uniqueness of the function name in the file.
3474 * A file could contain a function prototype and a function definition
3475 * or even multiple function prototypes.
3476 */
3477 bool found=FALSE;
3478 MemberName *mn;
3479 MemberDef *md_found=0;
3480 if ((mn=Doxygen::functionNameLinkedMap->find(rname)))
3481 {
3482 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("function '{}' already found",rname);
3483 for (const auto &imd : *mn)
3484 {
3485 MemberDefMutable *md = toMemberDefMutable(imd.get());
3486 if (md)
3487 {
3488 const NamespaceDef *mnd = md->getNamespaceDef();
3489 NamespaceDef *rnd = 0;
3490 //printf("root namespace=%s\n",qPrint(rootNav->parent()->name()));
3491 QCString fullScope = scope;
3492 QCString parentScope = root->parent()->name;
3493 if (!parentScope.isEmpty() && !leftScopeMatch(parentScope,scope))
3494 {
3495 if (!scope.isEmpty()) fullScope.prepend("::");
3496 fullScope.prepend(parentScope);
3497 }
3498 //printf("fullScope=%s\n",qPrint(fullScope));
3499 rnd = getResolvedNamespace(fullScope);
3500 const FileDef *mfd = md->getFileDef();
3501 QCString nsName,rnsName;
3502 if (mnd) nsName = mnd->name();
3503 if (rnd) rnsName = rnd->name();
3504 //printf("matching arguments for %s%s %s%s\n",
3505 // qPrint(md->name()),md->argsString(),qPrint(rname),qPrint(argListToString(root->argList)));
3506 const ArgumentList &mdAl = md->argumentList();
3507 const ArgumentList &mdTempl = md->templateArguments();
3508
3509 // in case of template functions, we need to check if the
3510 // functions have the same number of template parameters

3512 bool matchingReturnTypes = TRUE;
3513 bool sameRequiresClause = TRUE;
3514 if (!mdTempl.empty() && !root->tArgLists.empty())
3515 {
3516 if (mdTempl.size()!=root->tArgLists.back().size())
3517 {
3518 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3519 }
3520 if (md->typeString()!=removeRedundantWhiteSpace(root->type))
3521 {
3522 matchingReturnTypes = FALSE;
3523 }
3524 if (md->requiresClause()!=root->req)
3525 {
3526 sameRequiresClause = FALSE;
3527 }
3528 }
3529 else if (!mdTempl.empty() || !root->tArgLists.empty())
3530 { // if one has template parameters and the other doesn't then that also counts as a
3531 // difference
3532 sameNumTemplateArgs = FALSE;
3533 }

3536 root->isStatic && md->isStatic() && root->fileName!=md->getDefFileName();

3538 if (
3539 matchArguments2(md->getOuterScope(),mfd,&mdAl,
3540 rnd ? rnd : Doxygen::globalScope,rfd,&root->argList,
3541 FALSE,root->lang) &&
3542 sameNumTemplateArgs &&
3543 matchingReturnTypes &&
3544 sameRequiresClause &&
3545 !staticsInDifferentFiles
3546 )
3547 {
3548 GroupDef *gd=0;
3549 if (!root->groups.empty() && !root->groups.front().groupname.isEmpty())
3550 {
3551 gd = Doxygen::groupLinkedMap->find(root->groups.front().groupname);
3552 }
3553 //printf("match!\n");
3554 //printf("mnd=%p rnd=%p nsName=%s rnsName=%s\n",mnd,rnd,qPrint(nsName),qPrint(rnsName));
3555 // see if we need to create a new member
3556 found=(mnd && rnd && nsName==rnsName) || // members are in the same namespace
3557 ((mnd==0 && rnd==0 && mfd!=0 && // no external reference and
3558 mfd->absFilePath()==root->fileName // prototype in the same file
3559 )
3560 );
3561 // otherwise, allow a duplicate global member with the same argument list
3562 if (!found && gd && gd==md->getGroupDef() && nsName==rnsName)
3563 {
3564 // member is already in the group, so we don't want to add it again.
3565 found=TRUE;
3566 }
3567
3568 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("combining function with prototype found={} in namespace '{}'",found,nsName);
3569
3570 if (found)
3571 {
3572 // merge argument lists
3573 ArgumentList mergedArgList = root->argList;
3574 mergeArguments(const_cast<ArgumentList&>(mdAl),mergedArgList,!root->doc.isEmpty());
3575 // merge documentation
3576 if (md->documentation().isEmpty() && !root->doc.isEmpty())
3577 {
3578 if (root->proto)
3579 {
3580 md->moveDeclArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3581 }
3582 else
3583 {
3584 md->moveArgumentList(stringToArgumentList(root->lang,root->args));
3585 }
3586 }
3587
3588 md->setDocumentation(root->doc,root->docFile,root->docLine);
3589 md->setInbodyDocumentation(root->inbodyDocs,root->inbodyFile,root->inbodyLine);
3590 md->setDocsForDefinition(!root->proto);
3591 if (md->getStartBodyLine()==-1 && root->bodyLine!=-1)
3592 {
3593 md->setBodySegment(root->startLine,root->bodyLine,root->endBodyLine);
3594 md->setBodyDef(rfd);
3595 }
3596
3597 if (md->briefDescription().isEmpty() && !root->brief.isEmpty())
3598 {
3599 md->setArgsString(root->args);
3600 }
3601 md->setBriefDescription(root->brief,root->briefFile,root->briefLine);
3602
3603 md->addSectionsToDefinition(root->anchors);
3604
3605 md->enableCallGraph(md->hasCallGraph() || root->callGraph);
3606 md->enableCallerGraph(md->hasCallerGraph() || root->callerGraph);
3607 md->enableReferencedByRelation(md->hasReferencedByRelation() || root->referencedByRelation);
3608 md->enableReferencesRelation(md->hasReferencesRelation() || root->referencesRelation);
3609 md->addQualifiers(root->qualifiers);
3610
3611 // merge ingroup specifiers
3612 if (md->getGroupDef()==0 && !root->groups.empty())
3613 {
3614 addMemberToGroups(root,md);
3615 }
3616 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && root->groups.empty())
3617 {
3618 //printf("existing member is grouped, new member not\n");
3619 }
3620 else if (md->getGroupDef()!=0 && !root->groups.empty())
3621 {
3622 //printf("both members are grouped\n");
3623 }
3624
3625 // if md is a declaration and root is the corresponding
3626 // definition, then turn md into a definition.
3627 if (md->isPrototype() && !root->proto)
3628 {
3629 md->setDeclFile(md->getDefFileName(),md->getDefLine(),md->getDefColumn());
3630 md->setPrototype(FALSE,root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3631 }
3632 // if md is already the definition, then add the declaration info
3633 else if (!md->isPrototype() && root->proto)
3634 {
3635 md->setDeclFile(root->fileName,root->startLine,root->startColumn);
3636 }
3637 }
3638 }
3639 }
3640 if (found)
3641 {
3642 md_found = md;
3643 break;
3644 }
3645 }
3646 }
3647 if (!found) /* global function is unique with respect to the file */
3648 {
3649 addGlobalFunction(root,rname,scope);
3650 }
3651 else
3652 {
3653 FileDef *fd=root->fileDef();
3654 if (fd)
3655 {
3656 // add member to the file (we do this even if we have already
3657 // inserted it into the namespace)
3658 fd->insertMember(md_found);
3659 }
3660 }
3661
3662 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("unrelated function type='{}' name='{}' args='{}'",root->type,rname,root->args);
3663 }
3664 else
3665 {
3666 AUTO_TRACE_ADD("function '{}' is not processed",rname);
3667 }
3668 }
3669 else if (rname.isEmpty())
3670 {
3671 warn(root->fileName,root->startLine,
3672 "Illegal member name found."
3673 );
3674 }
3675 }
3676 for (const auto &e : root->children()) buildFunctionList(e.get());
3677}

12088 {

12090 n2->memberName().data()+getPrefixIndex(n2->memberName())
12091 )<0;
12092 };
12093
12094 auto classComp = [](const ClassLinkedMap::Ptr &c1,const ClassLinkedMap::Ptr &c2)
12095 {
12096 if (Config_getBool(SORT_BY_SCOPE_NAME))
12097 {
12098 return qstricmp(c1->name(), c2->name())<0;
12099 }
12100 else
12101 {
12102 int i = qstricmp(c1->className(), c2->className());
12103 return i==0 ? qstricmp(c1->name(), c2->name())<0 : i<0;
12104 }
12105 };
12106

12108 {
12109 return qstricmp(n1->name(),n2->name())<0;
12110 };
12111
12112 auto conceptComp = [](const ConceptLinkedMap::Ptr &c1,const ConceptLinkedMap::Ptr &c2)
12113 {
12114 return qstricmp(c1->name(),c2->name())<0;
12115 };

◆ processTagLessClasses()

static void processTagLessClasses ( const ClassDef *  rootCd,
const ClassDef *  cd,
ClassDefMutable *  tagParentCd,
const QCString &  prefix,
int  count 
)
static

Look through the members of class cd and its public members.

If there is a member m of a tag less struct/union, then we create a duplicate of the struct/union with the name of the member to identify it. So if cd has name S, then the tag less struct/union will get name S.m Since tag less structs can be nested we need to call this function recursively. Later on we need to patch the member types so we keep track of the hierarchy of classes we create.
